  <h2>What to Watch For</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Wet, soggy or spongy ground over the field with no recent rain.</li>
    <li>Unusually lush, green grass in a stripe or patch over the field.</li>
    <li>Odors over the field area.</li>
    <li>Slow drains or backups that return after pumping.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Why Early Action Matters</h2>
  <p>
    Field problems sit at the expensive end of septic ownership, so acting early genuinely pays. A <a href="/drain-field-repair-cookeville-tn/">drain-field evaluation</a> identifies what is happening before it grows. If you are seeing these signs, <a href="/request-service/">request septic service</a>.
  </p>

